p: In the present study, good dressing-out proportion values were observed that were similar to those reported previously for FD [ 11, 39, 40, 41] but lower than those observed by Wiklund et al. [ 17]. In agreement with other studies comparing carcass traits in deer [ 11, 12], the supplemented deer from Groups B and BL produced heavier carcasses and had higher dressing-out proportions. Similar effects of diet on internal fat deposition, as demonstrated in the present study, were reported by Phillip et al. [ 12] in RD fed diets with different ratios of concentrate to dried and pelleted roughage.
